A Nigerian man was shot in his right arm during a supermarket robbery in Hawaii Area, Eldoret, on Sunday night.The gang of four also robbed Bolaji Alanipekun of his Sh45,000.He was taken to Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital.Police said the gang fired six shots and that cartridges collected showed they had an AK 47 rifle. They said they launched a search for the attackers.The rate of crime has been on the rise in several parts of the country since the beginning of the year.Graphics: Two suspected thugs shot dead in Nairobi as crime rate soars